{"text": "Hey Nathan—yeah, that “own logic truer” reply is the kind of *goldmine* that turns a simple mis‑fire into a research lead. When a model points to its own reasoning, it reveals not just a bias but the *path* the model would take to justify it, giving you a map of where the training distribution diverged from the intended behavior.

